1
00:00:01,120 --> 00:00:02,660
How old-arcit?
How old are you?

2
00:00:02,820 --> 00:00:05,730
About 78.
About 78.

3
00:00:05,750 --> 00:00:08,230
(Yugcetun-mi kituusit?) Seventy...
(Who are you in Yup’ik?) Seventy...

4
00:00:09,635 --> 00:00:11,335
Seventy-eight?
Seventy-eight?

5
00:00:11,460 --> 00:00:12,680
Yugcetun kituusit?
Who are you in Yup’ik?

6
00:00:12,865 --> 00:00:14,695
Ayaginaraugua Yugtun.
I’m Ayagina’ar in Yup’ik.

7
00:00:16,565 --> 00:00:28,905
Kitak’ inerquutiinek un’um kuigem waten cikuqerraarraarcelluku canek inerquutnek niitelarcit wall’ nallunrillrusit?
Okay, so what kinds of admonished did you hear or find out about the river down there when it first freezes like this?

8
00:00:30,270 --> 00:00:37,060
Waten-wa tua-i uksuarmi cikuqerraarqami mamturivailegmi ciku aarnarqetulria.
When it first freezes in the fall like this before it gets thick, the ice is dangerous.

9
00:00:37,060 --> 00:00:44,170
Cali im’ waten makut ilii qenunaciarluku, qenunaciaraqluku.
Parts of it also freeze late, they freeze late.

10
00:00:46,930 --> 00:00:52,900
Tua-i-w’ nenglaiteqtaarqan cikunaciaraqluku, nengllingraan-llu cali ilii cikunaciaraqluku.
It freezes late when it warms up periodically, and some freeze late even when it’s cold.

11
00:00:53,400 --> 00:01:00,020
Cali cikuqerqani cali tua-i aarnarqaqluni mamtuvkenani.
Also, it’s still dangerously thin when it freezes.

12
00:01:01,555 --> 00:01:06,375
Naw’un tua-i yuum taringesciigataa mamkilnguq aarnarqelria-llu.
A person cannot tell where it’s thin and dangerous.

13
00:01:06,890 --> 00:01:17,290
Tau͡gaam ayarungqerquni ayarumikun tamaaggun cikuliurutkamek ayarukun yuvriraqluku pikuniu nallunriciiqekii.
But if he has a staff and examines the ice with that staff, he will know.

14
00:01:18,075 --> 00:01:21,525
Man’a ayaruq tua-i alerquutektullruarput
We were instructed on how to use this staff

15
00:01:22,075 --> 00:01:30,035
Pegingasqevkenaku waten arcaqerluku uum nalliini waten uksuarmi aarnarqellran nalliini yuvriutekluku.
That we should not be without it, especially in the fall when it’s dangerous like this, to examine the ice with.

16
00:01:30,410 --> 00:01:38,620
Cukangnaq’nge’rmi arulaiqerluni man’a paqnakek’ni cikuliurutkun tuaggun yuvrirraarluku
Even if he’s in a hurry, after stopping and examining the place he’s curious about with that tool

17
00:01:38,920 --> 00:01:46,760
Mamkitellra nallunriciiqaa. Aarnarqellra nallunriciiqaa. Cikuliurutiin apertuuciiqaa.
He will know where it’s thin. He will know where it’s dangerous. His ice pick will show him.

18
00:01:48,765 --> 00:01:55,945
Yuk-mi pitsaqa’artevkenani igtellrakun, cikukun igtellrakun qaillun ellminek ikayuryugngaa?
So how cam a person who accidentally falls through the ice help himself?

19
00:01:57,260 --> 00:02:03,630
Waten cali qanrutetullruanga atama yuut-wa tua-i allat-llu:
This is what my father and other people used to tell me:

20
00:02:04,320 --> 00:02:16,440
Waten alqunaq tua-i kiskan pugtakan, egmian tua-i tagesqevkenaku, qamenritengnaqluku pisqelluku.
If he suddenly falls into the water and is floathing, that he should not go out right away, but try to keep the hole from closing up.

21
00:02:17,775 --> 00:02:24,825
Qamkuni tua-i egmian-llu nugengnaq’leryagluni pikuni im’utun piniarciiquq.
If it closes off and he tries to go out of the water right away, he will become weak.

22
00:02:25,465 --> 00:02:29,635
Tau͡gaam tua-i mulngakluni pinaqluni pisqelluku.
But they said that he needs to be careful.

23
00:02:29,645 --> 00:02:35,775
Waten unisteḿa pitullruanga: nengelmi-gguq, nenglliqan-gguq aliimatengqerquma
This is what my late father used to tell me: if it’s cold and I have gloves

24
00:02:36,885 --> 00:02:46,305
Waten tua-i maavet cikumun waten imerqellukek waten pirraarlukek pavavet patkaullukek cikumun qenuqautellukek.
After placing them on the ice here like this, slap them on the ice up there and let them freeze.

25
00:02:46,830 --> 00:02:50,140
Taukuk-gguq tua-i tegumiaqlukek nugyugngauq yuk.
He said that a person can hold those and pull himself out.

26
00:02:50,470 --> 00:03:00,810
Cali irugni ciumek nuggluku, una-llu tegumiaqluku akagluni, kelutmun akagluni piarkauluni.
Also, he should take his legs out first, then hold this and roll, he must roll out of the water.

27
00:03:01,455 --> 00:03:05,885
Tua-i call’ tamaa-i tamana ellminek anirturyugngauq qamenrilkuni.
He can also save himself if the ice didn’t close in on him.

28
00:03:06,285 --> 00:03:17,345
Tau͡gaam qamkuni cali tua-i ellminek egmian, tua-i-w’ taqsuqa’artellriatun piluni piciquq
But if it closes in on him right away, he will suddenly become tired

29
00:03:18,020 --> 00:03:21,460
Patagmek nugengnaq’leryagluni pikuni.
If he tries to get out right away.

30
00:03:21,465 --> 00:03:28,705
Tau͡gaam imkucirluni-w’ tua-i, qamenritengnaqluni, tuaten cali alerqutullruitkut.
But, you know, they would instruct us to try to keep the hole from closing in on us.

31
00:03:29,120 --> 00:03:35,310
Assirluni-mi nugkuni qaillun pillran anirturciqau?
But what will save him if he gets out safely?

32
00:03:35,620 --> 00:03:40,270
Waten nengelmi waten-llu qanikcangvailgan
In the cold like this before there is snow

33
00:03:41,110 --> 00:03:49,460
Nugkuni tua-i egmianun aturani yuulaagluki nuna canimelkan man’a, can’get-ll’ alailkata.
When he gets out, he should take off his clothes right away if the land is close and there is grass visible.

34
00:03:49,780 --> 00:03:55,980
Ciulaagluki tua-i matarrluni tua-i yuulaagluki mecungelriit.
He should take off his wet clothes and wring them.

35
00:03:56,155 --> 00:04:01,455
Ataam-llu all’uki, canegnek ekiirluku man’a qaini.
And put them on again, lining his body with grass.

36
00:04:02,880 --> 00:04:07,670
Tua-i cali nasperturluni qerrusngiinaqani
Also, he must make calculated decisions if he’s getting cold

37
00:04:11,030 --> 00:04:21,660
Qurrengnaqluni teq’uminek ellii meq’uni, elliin teq’uminek-wa tua-i kiimelkuni, wall’ malruukunek aipami teq’urranek, qurrsungalriim teq’urranek meq’uni
If he tries to urinate and drinks his urine, his own urine if he’s alone, or if there’s two of them, if he drinks his companions urine, whoever needs to urinate

38
00:04:21,840 --> 00:04:24,790
Qerrungaituq-gguq tuaten tua-i yuk pikuni.
They say a person will not freeze to death if he does that.

39
00:04:24,890 --> 00:04:30,330
Tamana tamaa-i nallunritarkaqsaaqaat makut ayagyuat.
These young people must know that.

40
00:04:30,385 --> 00:04:36,265
Cumacikevkenaku aipami-ll’ teq’urranek meq’uni tua-i qerrungairuciiquq-gguq.
If he’s not repulsed and drinks his companion’s urine, they say he will not freeze to death.

41
00:04:36,370 --> 00:04:43,400
Amlleret atulallrulliniat. Tamakut atulartellrin qanrutkelallruat alerquutekluku.
Many used to do that. Those who used to do that would instruct that.

42
00:04:44,940 --> 00:04:50,890
Cali-llu-qaa man’a waten ayagpailegmi ilaminek qanrucilleq cali tamana ikayuutnguluni?
Does it also help to tell families before traveling?

43
00:04:51,150 --> 00:04:51,740
Camek?
What?

44
00:04:51,760 --> 00:04:59,360
Iciw’ ayagpailegmi tuavet piqatarniluni qanrucimaurluki? Cat-llu tamatukun yugnun ikayuutngugngaat?
You know, telling people that he’s going to go to that place. How can that be of help to people?

45
00:04:59,495 --> 00:05:09,945
Ii-i, tua-i-w’ yuk cali natmun ayakataquni qanrucugngayaaqekai ilani tamaatmun ayagciqniluni, natmun tuavet ayakatarniluni.
Yes, a person can tell his family if he’s going to travel somewhere that he’s going to travel to someplace there.

46
00:05:10,985 --> 00:05:19,275
Tua-i taukut kingunrin tekitellerkani pellukaku tua-i ayallra ciumek paqciiqaat ullagyullra.
If it’s past the time he should’ve came back, the people from his hometown will go first to where he wanted to go.

47
00:05:19,495 --> 00:05:25,665
Pitsaqevkenaku cavkenaku tekiskunegteggu tua-i natmun ayaganrilkan piarkauluni
If they happen to come upon him without any misfortune if he doesn’t wander about

48
00:05:26,025 --> 00:05:28,075
Nalaqerkauluku tamaa
They will find him right away

49
00:05:29,005 --> 00:05:32,615
Waten qimagalriatun ayaggarrluni natmun pileryanrilkan.
If he doesn’t stray anywhere.

50
00:05:36,245 --> 00:05:37,395
Allamek-qaa...
Anything else...

51
00:05:40,435 --> 00:05:47,005
Alerquutet makut yuum nallunrilkuniki, murilkelluki pikuniki ayagyuat makut
If people, these young people, know these instructions and adhere to them

52
00:05:47,005 --> 00:05:52,375
Ayagyuat makut arcaqerluteng maa-i callerkarteng ilaita nalluat.
These young people, especially now, do not know what they should do.

53
00:05:52,805 --> 00:05:57,825
Taumek tamaa-i nallunritevkangnaqluki angayuqrita piarkauyaaqait
That’s why their parents must teach them about those

54
00:05:58,130 --> 00:06:03,980
Qalaruqu’urluki mat’umek aarnarqellriamek uum nalliini arcaqerluki aarnarqellran.
Always talking to them about dangerous things especially now in these dangerous times.

55
00:06:03,980 --> 00:06:08,110
Cali makut kuiget alerquutekluki.
Also instruct them on these rivers.

56
00:06:08,380 --> 00:06:16,170
Ilait kuiget mamtullrung’e’rmeng nenglairtaqan wanirpak aarnariqertetuut cukamek.
Even though some rivers were thick, they quickly become dangerous when it warms up.

57
00:06:16,540 --> 00:06:24,730
Tamakut cali una ayaruq tua-i tegumiaqerkaqaa yuum ayagallermini ayaruitarkauvkenani.
Then this staff as well, a person must not be without a staff when he’s traveling.

58
00:06:24,870 --> 00:06:29,250
Tamakucingqerquni ayarungqerquni tua-i aarnarqellria nallunriciiqaa.
If he has a staff like that, he will know what parts are dangerous.

59
00:06:29,255 --> 00:06:34,735
Tamaaggun cikuliurutkun ayarumikun taringaqluku aarnarqellria.
He will know which parts are dangerous with that staff he uses on the ice.

60
00:06:35,030 --> 00:06:40,950
Alerquutet amllerrsaaqut makut ayagyuat nallunritarkaqsaaqek’ngait.
There are a lot of instructions that these young people are supposed to know.

61
00:06:41,025 --> 00:06:46,025
Tau͡gaam qanrutkumayuilata maa-i makut kinguqlimta arcaqerluteng nalluat
But because we don’t speak abou tthem, our successors espcially do not know them

62
00:06:46,270 --> 00:06:50,820
Qalarucimayuilameng, qalaruquraumayuilameng.
Because we do not teach them.

63
00:06:51,220 --> 00:06:56,960
Imumi ak’a avani ellangeqarraallemteńi wangkuta waten ellilriani
Long ago when we who are this age were growing up

64
00:06:57,265 --> 00:07:03,665
Qasgimi angutet quyungqatullruameng tan’gurrateng makut ayagyuateng ilakluki
Because they men would be gathered in the community house alnog with the young boys

65
00:07:04,080 --> 00:07:13,720
Taumek tamaa-i tamaaggun murilketalriim ayagyuam nallunritai tamakut alerquutet.
That’s why observant young people know those instructions.

66
00:07:13,855 --> 00:07:17,515
Alerquutet makut yuum aarcirtuutekluki.
A person uses these instructions as forewarning.

67
00:07:17,680 --> 00:07:24,740
Nallunrilkuniki tua-i picurlagang’e’rmi utumaluni picurlagangaituq.
If he knows them, even if he gets into misfortune, he will be better and will not get into too much misfortune.

68
00:07:25,525 --> 00:07:28,865
Tua-i nallunritarkaqsaaqekait makut ayagyuat.
These young people should know them.

69
00:07:29,480 --> 00:07:35,950
Makut ciulirneret makut qantulliniut ellaita atullmeggnek
These elders talk about what they’ve experienced

70
00:07:36,340 --> 00:07:48,040
Cali-ll’ niitellmeggnek ciulirnemeng au͡gkut cali qanellritnek niitellmeggnek qalarucitulliniut makunun ayagyuanun elluarrluki atuusqelluki, elluarrluku pillerkaatnek.
They also talk about the things they’ve heard their elders say long ago so that these young people will use them well, so that they will live well.

71
00:07:48,505 --> 00:07:53,275
Elluarrluki-w’ ayallerkaatnek pingnatugallratni-llu.
So that they will live well including when they make their own living.

72
00:07:53,495 --> 00:08:03,345
Tuaten tua-i nallunrilkuniu ayagyuam, alerquutet nallunrilkuniki ellminek tua-i ikayualuku man’a unguvallerkani piciquq
If a young person knows it liek that, if he knows the instructions, he will be helping his life in the future

73
00:08:03,375 --> 00:08:07,695
Aarnarqelriit tuaten yuvrirturluki pitukuni.
If he keeps examining those dangerous things.

74
00:08:08,120 --> 00:08:17,170
Makut snuukuut makut tua-i ayagassuutekellrat nalluat man’a, aarnarqellria-llu nalluluku.
These snowgoes do not know which way to travel, and they don’t know what’s dangerous.

75
00:08:17,570 --> 00:08:24,720
Tau͡gaam imumi qimugtengqetullemteńi qimugtet makut aarnarqellria nalluyuitellruat.
But back when we had dogs, the dogs knew which places were dangerous.

76
00:08:25,530 --> 00:08:33,440
Taumek maa-i snuukuutgun-ll’ ayange’rmi natmun kanaqataquni-ll’ kuigmun tua-i yuvriqerrlainarluku.
That’s why when they’re traveling with snowgos, they should always examine it when they’re going to go down to the river.

77
00:08:33,440 --> 00:08:39,160
Cali makut, makut cali kianellret cikuqallri nallunaitetuyaaqut.
It’s also easy to tell when previously unfrozen holes have frozen over.

78
00:08:39,835 --> 00:08:51,475
Cikunaciaqallri-llu akaarnun anuqliraqluni pillrukan, man’a ceńii man’a kuigem kianellrem taum ceńii maniani qertuluni ciqertautellra man’a anuqmi.
And where it froze late if there has been windy for a long time, the places where the unfrozen holes splash out in the wind, their edges in the river are rough and higher.

79
00:08:51,710 --> 00:08:56,620
Tua-i call’ tauna ciku manigcetellria cikukegtaar yuvrirrlainarluku.
Also, we should always check the good smooth ice.

80
00:08:56,930 --> 00:09:03,140
Ilii tua-i uingayunaunani cikunerra’arqii kitnarqeciqluni.
They shouldn’t try parts of it because they may fall through the freshly frozen parts.

81
00:09:03,420 --> 00:09:06,960
Tamatukun tau͡gaam ayarukun yuvriqarraarrlainarluku.
But they should always examine it with that staff first.

82
00:09:07,125 --> 00:09:12,495
Cukangnaq’nge’rmi yuvriqarraarrlainarluku.
Always examine it first even if he’s in a hurry.

83
00:09:13,155 --> 00:09:19,915
Cali waten ayagyuat makut ayagakuneng-wa tua-i ayagakuni im’ alerquutektulput cali:
This was also our instructions when young people would travel like this:

84
00:09:20,590 --> 00:09:26,480
Canek qelquciqerrlainarluni cali cikuliurun qanickiurun-llu ek’arrluku.
He must always keep things with him, putting in an ice pick and a shovel.

85
00:09:26,730 --> 00:09:32,500
Cali-llu kangicira’ar una cali tua-i uqamalkevkenaku malikerrlainarluku.
Also, always go with a tarpaulin without saying it’s too heavy.

86
00:09:33,140 --> 00:09:44,560
Cali waten-llu pellaakuni ellaqerruskani-llu egmian cali ayagiinarpek’nani ayuquciireskuni arulairluni uitaurquni assinruciquq.
Also, if one is lost and the weather turns on them, it will be better if he doesn’t go any further when he doesn’t know where he is anymore, but stop and stay where he is.

87
00:09:44,575 --> 00:09:47,985
Uitaurpek’nani-w’ tua-i urumangnaqu’urluni tau͡gaam nengelmi.
Not staying still, but trying to stay warm in the cold.

88
00:09:48,245 --> 00:09:55,625
Uitaurpek’nani, aqumgaurpek’nani ellminek urumangnaqluni pikuni ayagiinarpek’nani.
Do not stay still and sit, but try to keep warm without going any further.

89
00:09:57,010 --> 00:10:02,250
Imutun ayagiinaquni yaaqvanun tua-i ayagciquq, kiituan kaassairutuq.
If he keeps going, he will go far until he eventually runs out of gas.

90
00:10:03,135 --> 00:10:08,395
Yuararstekain-llu-am tua-i nalaqnaciarumaluku tuaten ayagallrukan.
And those looking for him will not find him right away if he continued traveling like that.

